Mrs. Mcfarland presents to GI for staging and evaluation of her distal rectal cancer.  Had a very frank discussion with the patient.  At this time, we will proceed with staging CT abdomen and pelvis and endoscopic ultrasound after which she will me with Dr. Cooper from Colon & Rectal Surgery.  She will also meet with  a stomal therapist for education purposes.  Her outside PET will be sent to Radiology along with the MRI.  We discussed the role of preoperative chemoradiation if T3 of N1 disease is noted.  Patient would be interested in laparoscopic surgery if this is possible.
